## Sheet 4: Break-Even Analysis
| Input Parameters | Values |
|------------------|--------|
| Fixed Costs | $100,000 |
| Variable Cost per Unit | $15 |
| Selling Price per Unit | $25 |
| Target Profit | $50,000 |

### Break-Even Calculations
| Metric | Formula | Value |
|--------|---------|-------|
| Contribution Margin | =Selling_Price - Variable_Cost | $10 |
| Break-Even Units | =Fixed_Costs / Contribution_Margin | 10,000 |
| Break-Even Revenue | =Break_Even_Units * Selling_Price | $250,000 |
| Units for Target Profit | =(Fixed_Costs + Target_Profit) / Contribution_Margin | 15,000 |
| Revenue for Target Profit | =Units_for_Target_Profit * Selling_Price | $375,000 |

